out_desc_tool: Combined High achieveing heterogeneous v high homogeneous and Low Heterogeneous v Low homogeneous Posttest. The purpose of the application test de- signed for this study was to determine whether there was a significant difference between the experimental and control sec- tions in their ability to utilize and apply meteorological information. The applica- tion test (reliability .So), employed the use of materials with which a pupil might come in daily contact. The material for the items was obtained from such sources as 2x2 color slides of cloud formations, articles with reference to weather found in current newspapers and popular periodicals, and weather forecast maps as illustrated in daily newspapers.
